    • Uses of Technical in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Items.interfaces

      Subinterfaces of Technical in com.planet_ink.coffee_mud.Items.interfaces 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  Computer
      A computer is a particular type of electronics panel that holds software, and has readers who monitor the messages this panel generates, as well as use the Type command to enter data into this panel's software.
      interface  ElecPanel
      An interface for a particular kind of container that is invisible when closed, holds particular kinds of electrical gear, and allows some level of manipulation of the items inside.
      interface  Electronics
      Electronics are items that can be turned on and off before their interesting behavior or ability is available, which requires "power" to be operated, and has some capacitance for power that keeps it running for some dramatic amount of time while it is no longer receiving new power.
      interface  FuelConsumer
      An interface for an Electrical item that also consumes some other sort of fuel other than electrical power, if it consumes any electricity at all.
      interface  PowerGenerator
      An interface that combines both a PowerSource and and FuelConsumer to produce a Power Generator, or converter from fuel to electricity.
      interface  PowerSource
      An interface for an Electrical item that produces rather than consumes power, though it may consume something else to generate that power.
      interface  ShipEngine
      A ShipEngine is a special TechComponent that is often a fuel consumer, and which has special tracked attributes related to its ability to propel a ship and, usually, consume fuel.
      interface  ShipWarComponent
      A ship war component can be a gun or a shield generator.
      interface  Software
      Software is a plain technical item that monitors and manipulates other space ship components and systems, while also managing a user interface for players/mobs monitoring the software.
      interface  TechComponent
      A TechComponent is a type of electronics item that must be installed into a panel that can accept it.
